<font color="#FF0000">CANNON FODDER</font><br>
<tt>Wed Feb  5 13:33:25 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Criticized with pungent hatred by some white Vietnam veterans for its revealing exposure of racism, yet admired by many white vets for its honesty, Cannon Foddder: Growing Up For Vietnam, tells the experience of a young, African-American who evolved to serve his country in Vietnam. &quot;Some white vets left the Constitution at home when they said goodbye to their families&quot;, the author writes. My Lai and other atrocities committed by white officers and their men should have been no surprise. Vietnam, for many of these men, was the American Civil War war... again to be lost. http://members.aol.com/veterans/cf.htm
<p><code>-- veterans@pacbell.net  (Brooke Rowe) </code><p>


